  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Compliance Intern (1 Year)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job purpose:</strong></p><p>This is an entry level role for a fresh graduate or undergraduate joining our Compliance Team for QA & Governance International <strong>for 1-year</strong>. We are offering the opportunity to gain exposure to various Compliance related tasks covered by the Singapore located QA & Governance Team for the Asian region and beyond. </p><p><strong>Key activities :</strong></p><p>The candidate’s responsibility will include:</p><ul><li>preparation, organisation, administration of meetings and reporting,</li><li>assistance for QA and Control execution,</li><li>aid with project related tasks,</li><li>liaise with local Compliance Officers and Head Office on various topics and</li><li>assist the Regional Head of Compliance Asia and the Head of Compliance QA & Gov. International with ad-hoc tasks.</li></ul><p><strong>Formal education:</strong></p><p>Vocational training, Polytechnic diploma, university degree or similar, preferably in Banking, Business Management. University undergraduates welcomed.</p><p><strong>Specialist knowledge (work experience, further qualification):</strong></p><p>Work Experience:</p><ul><li>Fresh graduates with not more than 1 year of professional work experience (excluding internships)</li><li>Relevant work/internship experience within a financial institution or similar an advantage</li><li>General understanding of the banking industry</li></ul><p>Further qualification/skills:</p><ul><li>Fluent in English; German an advantage</li><li>Good written and communication skills with ability to develop a strong working partnership with internal stakeholders of various level from different departments;</li><li>Team player and demonstrate ability to work independently, under pressure and proactively;</li><li>Possess good analytical skills, detailed oriented and is dependable in work assigned</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Powerpoint and Excel;</li></ul>",
